Q. Smoke Testing

Purpose: To check whether the major functionalities of the application are 
working and the build is stable enough for further testing.

When: After a new build is deployed
Scope: Broad / high-level
Example:
Can the login page open? ✅
Are the main menu items working? ✅
Does the app crash on launch?

Q. Sanity Testing

Purpose: To verify that a specific functionality or bug fix is working as expected
When: After a minor change or bug fix
Scope: Narrow / focused

Example:
A login bug was fixed → test only the login feature
Payment module fix → test only the payment flow

